        "Problem Statement 9- A factory produces 1000 mobile phones per day, out of which 20 are defective.\n",
        "Find the probability of selecting a defective and a non-defective phone.\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3qqyE485Bm7c"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "total_phones=10000\n",
        "defective_phones=20\n",
        "p_defective=defective_phones/total_phones\n",
        "p_non_defective=1-p_defective\n",
        "print(\"Total phones=\",total_phones)\n",
        "print(\"Defective phones=\",defective_phones)\n",
        "print(\"\\n Probability of defectuve phone=\",p_defective)\n",
        "print(\"\\n Probability of non-defective phone=\",p_non_defective)\n",
        "print(\"\\n percentage of defective phones=\",p_defective*100,\"%\")\n",
        "print(\"percentage of non-defective phones=\",p_non_defective*100,\"%\")"
      ],
